text.tspan: Share of bilateral and unilateral trade partnerships around the world
To construct this chart we started from a dataset with dyadic trade estimates. For each year we took all country
pairs with data and classified them as follows: "Non-trading" (pairs in which countries do not trade with
one-another); "Bilateral" (pairs in which both countries export to one-another); and "Unilateral" (pairs in which only
one country exports to the other).
